<br>
<br>
1. Tundra - Our unique RA style has a penalty for dual weilding. Our class is designed to be the main dual weilding (Left Axe) class for our realm. Obviously Left Axe and Tundra don't work too well together. Please find a way to have Tundra not penalized for dual weilding. If that won't work, there are many ideas on the boards for other types of abilities to replace it.<br>
<br>
2. Shape Shifting - I'm not talking about our Berserk ability here. I'm talking about the true implimentation of shapeshifting. Is there still a plan to implement a complete animal transformation? As I have not heard any recent word on this topic any information about it from Mythic would be welcome.<br>
<br>
3. Berserk Model - Many people would like to see a different model used when we go Berserk. The most common suggestion I have seen is a Fenrir.<br>
<br>
4. Aroura Borealis (LA L50 Style) - This style is based off an opponent parrying us. At this point it only works if our MAIN hand is parried, not our off hand. Please fix this particular bug so that the style works no matter which hand is parried. Many Zerkers are calling for a different trigger for this style, however I want to wait till the group parry/block bug gets fixed to see how that impacts the use of this style.<br>
<br>
5. Speed Increase During Berserk - When a Zerker goes Berserk in RvR a common tactic of our target is to sprint away. This usually results in the Zerk staying just outside of melee range and essentially wasting our Berserk. I'd like to see a percent increase to our run speed during Berserk. This would better allow us to catch fleeing opponents so we can at least get within melee range.<br>
<br>
6. Berserk When Dead/Sitting - Thanks to the recent patch that grays out buttons when an ability is not available this bug is not quite as annoying. Currently when a Zerker is dead or sitting and presses his Berserk button he will shapeshift and reset the 7 minute timer. Please fix this so that we get a message when dead or sitting that we cannot use this ability while dead or sitting.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
GENERAL ISSUES:<br>
<br>
<br>
1. Speed Increase During Charge - Similar to the speed increase I requested during Berserk, this would apply to all classes that get the Charge ability. This would just give us a higher chance to get into melee range before charge wears off.<br>
<br>
2. Prevent Flight - Several people have told me they would like to see the cost of Prevent Flight lowered from its current 14 point cost. This would be beneficial to all tank classes that recieve this RA as it would increase their chance (earlier in their carrer) to keep their target in melee range when they turn and run.<br>
<br>
3. Unique RA Styles - Just like the Zerker specific RA, Tundra, all the other dual weilding classes that recieve RA styles are penalized for dual weilding. Please fix this for all affected classes.<br>
<br>
4. Wasting RA Styles - If a target is out of range or not visible for any reason and you use your RA style it will waste it and reset the timer. Please fix this bug so that if you don't actually USE the style, it doesn't reset the timer.<br>
<br>
5. Parry/Block Bug - Please see the warrior report for a detailed explanation of this.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
IDEAS FOR GENERAL IMPROVEMENT:<br>
<br>
1. Parry Spec - I'd like to see some additional benefit come from speccing in Parry. Sheild users get an increased chance to block and also styles and group friendly abilities. If we could get some similar group friendly abilities come from speccing in Parry I think it would add to the group friendliness of tanks that can't spec in shield. Just to clarify, I DO NOT want to see any styles or offensive abilities granted for speccing in parry. Mostly just the ability to guard a fellow player and parry blows for them.<br>
